Exp 2: Working with Git Branches

1) Open a folder and create a new folder.
2) Copy the path of the folder.
3) Open Git Bash and paste the path using cd command.
4) git init
   -> To initialize Git in repository.

5) Create a file using command:
   notepad file1.txt

6) Notepad opens, type:
   this is initial content

7) Save and close the notepad.

8) Go to Git Bash and type:
   git add file1.txt

9) git commit -m "Initial commit"

10) Check current branch:
    git branch
    -> Git shows main or master.

11) Create feature branch:
    git branch feature-branch

12) Switch to feature branch:
    git checkout feature-branch

13) Modify file in feature branch:
    notepad file1.txt

14) Type:
    this is feature branch modification

15) Save and close the file.

16) git add file1.txt

17) git commit -m "Added new feature in feature branch"

18) Switch back to master/main branch:
    git checkout master

19) Modify file in master branch:
    notepad file1.txt

20) Type:
    this is main branch modification

21) git add file1.txt

22) git commit -m "Updated file in master branch"

23) Merge feature branch:
    git merge feature-branch
    -> Conflict occurs

24) Right click inside project folder
    -> Show more options
    -> Select TortoiseGit
    -> Resolve

25) Select file1.txt
    -> Edit conflicts

26) In TortoiseMerge:
    -> Right click on "mine" (file1-local)
    -> Select 3rd option (use block from right before left)
    -> Click Save

27) Close TortoiseMerge.

28) git add file1.txt
    -> Now conflict will not occur.

29) git status

30) git log

31) Delete feature branch (optional):
    git branch -d feature-branch
